body:
To reproduce this issue, check out [Ibex](https://github.com/lowRISC/ibex), e.g. version b295f07b (although this shouldn't be version-sensitive) and then run the synthesis flow. The instructions in `syn/README.md` should work.

The synthesis flow works by running sv2v and then running Yosys on the output. With the current head of the Yosys master branch, you get the following error message:
```
out/generated/ibex_cs_registers.v:544: ERROR: Non-constant function call in constant expression.
```
The relevant code looks like this:
```systemverilog
mstatus_d = {
   ... // some other elements in the concatenation
   sv2v_cast_2(sv2v_cast_2(csr_wdata_int[ibex_pkg_CSR_MSTATUS_MPP_BIT_HIGH:ibex_pkg_CSR_MSTATUS_MPP_BIT_LOW])),
   ... // some other elements in the concatenation
};
```
Here, `sv2v_cast_2` is defined as follows:
```systemverilog
	function automatic [1:0] sv2v_cast_2;
		input reg [1:0] inp;
		sv2v_cast_2 = inp;
	endfunction
```

Bisecting Yosys builds points to commit 2085d9a.

If you manually hack the generated code to replace the argument to the inner `sv2v_cast_2` with a constant like `8'b0` OR (more confusingly) remove one layer of `sv2v_cast_2` calls, the error message goes away.

@zachjs (since this was your change, and you probably also understand the output from sv2v better than me!)

